- Access types can include actions like view, download, etc.;
- The latest measurement and access are determined by the most recent timestamp and access_date, respectively.

- Active stations are those with a status of 'active';
- The most recently installed sensor at each station is determined by the installation date in descending order;
- The latest measurement for each sensor is determined by the timestamp in descending order.

- "measurement data" refers to data collected by sensors located at various stations;
- "accessed" means the data was viewed or downloaded by users;
- "stations" are locations where sensors are installed to collect data.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT al.user_id) AS distinct_users
FROM access_logs al
INNER JOIN users u ON al.user_id = u.user_id;

